xtual tradition of the excerpts from his work. Håkanson's Teubner text (1989) of Controversiae I is subsequently reprinted. The core of the volume is Håkanson's commentary, mostly - but not exclusively - devoted to textual elucidation. The volume closes with a bibliographical updating on the issues dealt with by Håkanson in the book, and an index locorum. With its keen insights and stimulating discussions, this publication appeals not only to scholars focussing on ancient rhetoric, but to anyone concerned with the culture of the Roman imperial era.   aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 27. Mrz 2018) 4aControversiae. 4aHåkanson, Lennart. 4aSeneca der Ältere. 4aSeneca the Elder.1 aCitti, Francesco, eeditor.1 aSantorelli, Biagio, eeditor.1 aStramaglia, Antonio, eeditor.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2016z9783110485103oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Classical Studies 2016z9783110485097oZDB-23-DGD0 cEPUBz978-3-11-049140-10 cprintz978311048783140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783110493061423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783110493061.jpg  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_CL  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA14ALL  aPDA16SSH  aPDA1ALL  aPDA2  aPDA2HUM  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGDb2016  aZDB-23-DGGb2016